    "recap_headline": "Boston College Athletics",
    "recap_text": "CHESTNUT HILL, Mass. \u2014\nBoston College Baseball (14-8, 4-3 ACC) defeated Cal (13-9, 0-4 ACC) in the first of three games this weekend, 4-3.\nA.J. Colarusso\nstarted and went six innings, allowing two earned runs while striking out two.\nCesar Gonzalez\ncame on in relief and went three scoreless innings, allowing just two hits en route to earning the win.\nThe Golden Bears got on the board first with a single to left field that scored a runner from second base and gave Cal the early 1-0 lead.\nThey would pick up a second in the top half of the next inning with a single to center, bringing in the runner from third to give the Golden Bears a two-run advantage.\nBoston College made it 2-1 in the bottom half of the inning when\nGunnar Johnson\nsingled in\nDanny Surowiec\nfrom second.\nCal would make it 3-1 in the top of the fourth when they launched a 402-foot home run to left center field.\nBoth defenses stood strong through the fifth and sixth innings, with the Eagles turning a double play to get out of a jam.\nIn the bottom of the seventh, Boston College tied the game at three courtesy of an RBI single from\nTy Mainolfi\nafter\nJulio Solier\nled the inning off with a triple. Mainolfi tied the game at three when a failed pick-off attempt went into center field, allowing him to score from third.\nIn the bottom of the eighth, the Eagles took the lead when\nColin Larson\nsingled home\nJace Roossien\nfrom second.\nGonzalez got the first two outs in the ninth and worked around two hits to get the final out and close out the game.\nUp Next:\nThe Eagles will return to action tomorrow at 1:00 p.m. for the second game of their series with the Golden Bears.",
